The paper discusses the use of bibliometric mapping techniques to investigate and represent perspectives on the innovation process, which involves analyzing large amounts of data. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and sound (cs.SD).
